rom xUnit.net v2 to xUnit.net v3. Here are the key changes:\n\n1. **Package references**: In xUnit v3, the package structure changes:\n   - `xunit` → `xunit.v3` (or `xunit.v3.core` + `xunit.v3.assert`)\n   - `xunit.runner.visualstudio` → `xunit.runner.visualstudio` v3 or the new runner\n   - `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` may still be needed or replaced\n\n2. **Project configuration**: xUnit v3 tests are executables, not libraries. \n\nThe test project needs to be configured as an executable with `<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>`, since the test runner is now built into the test project itself. I also need to drop `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` and `xunit.runner.visualstudio` since they're no longer required—the namespace stays as `Xunit`, but the overall structure and how tests execute has fundamentally changed.","outputTokens":1113,"requestId":"E3DE:52A37:797449:8BBDA8:6A052D7C"},"id":"7d5b79e4-c0b1-463b-8d38-a354b1cc8d65","timestamp":"2026-05-14T02:03:57.055Z","parentId":"9894e6c8-b9d9-482e-b8a5-19f5ce3c7b58"}
